{"title": "Creating New Patient Education", "body": "Creating New Patient Education\n  Although MediRecords will come pre-loaded with numerous Patient Education resources, you are able to upload new Patient Education resources in your MediRecords system, for use in your clinical consultations.\nThis article will briefly go through the steps to creating new patient education resources in MediRecords.\n\nWithin Patient Education, click New.\n\n\n\nYou will be shown the following popup:\n\n\n\nOf particular note are the Category and the Share fields. Category determines the classification of the new resource, and Share determines the privacy setting.\n\n\n\n\n\nClick Select File and you will be prompted to upload the resource from your device. Please make sure the file size does not exceed 10 MB, and the file type is either JPG, PNG or PDF.\n\n\n\nOnce all details have been filled in, the file is uploaded, and you have read the copyright notice, click Save. The following has been filled out as an example.\n\n\n\nYour new Patient Education resource will now be available for use.\nNeed assistance, please contact MediRecords support on 1300 103 903 during business hours OR email Support@medirecords.com "}